I really enjoy this one.  I love the dark twist and unique elements it has.  It is a good game to sit and mess around with when you want to be entertained while winding down.  I love the humor in the combinations and the implied throwbacks to many metaphors.  Some suggestions to improve it?  Add landscape orientation support.  Take a page from Doodle Farm and use the border hints:  Solid=Mixable, Dotted=Not right now, Grayed Out=Good as it gets.  Maybe make an option to 'share' completed elements that are the same in Doodle God with those that are in Doodle Devil; it would save some repetition.    As in Doodle God, and Doodle Farm, I like the quotes, the cute humor they contain, and really look forward to more from the Developers.  I'm an avid fan of the Doodle Trio!
